	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Windows' GUI is probably just being stupid.  Bust out cmd.exe, run FORMAT /?, and then try messing with options (e.g. FORMAT /FS:FAT /U driveletter:).  You DO NOT need to mess with cluster size (in fact with the PowerPak you should probably leave it at its default).

		

		</td>
